<p>I've created a simple web interface for my capturing device for a Webcam and a framegrabber. for capturing it works perfectly fine (this part is not my question) but I would also like to have the live streaming of both devices on the web interface as well.</p>  <p>For this purpose I'm using the flask web server and for getting one stream (from webcam) I could manage to use the code below. How can I get both streams (from /dev/video0 for webcam, and /dev/video1 for framegrabber) on the interface together(similar to the picture below)?</p>  <p>The result should be something like this in an html file at the end:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/098HU.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/098HU.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>This is the "camera.py" file:</p>  <pre><code>import cv2  class VideoCamera(object): def __init__(self):     # Using OpenCV to capture from device 0.      self.video = cv2.VideoCapture(0)      def __del__(self):     self.video.release()  def get_frame(self):     success, image = self.video.read()     images,      ret, jpeg = cv2.imencode('.jpg', image)     return jpeg.tostring() </code></pre>  <p>and here is the "main.py" file which runs on the server:</p>  <pre><code>from flask import Flask, render_template, Response from camera import VideoCamera  app = Flask(__name__)  @app.route('/') def index(): return render_template('index2.html')  def gen(camera): while True:     frame = camera.get_frame()     yield (b'--frame\r\n'            b'Content-Type: image/jpeg\r\n\r\n' + frame + b'\r\n\r\n')   @app.route('/video_feed') def video_feed(): return Response(gen(VideoCamera()),                 mimetype='multipart/x-mixed-replace; boundary=frame')  if __name__ == '__main__': app.run(host='0.0.0.0', debug=True) </code></pre>  <p>and here is the "index.html" file that loads the streamed video(for now it's only the stream of Webcam but I'd like to have framegrabbers' beside that):</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="column half"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;             &lt;div class="column half"&gt;                     &lt;div class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-4by3"&gt;                             &lt;iframe src="{{ url_for('video_feed') }}"     allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="210" width="300"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;                     &lt;/div&gt;             &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>